#risc-v test study

##tests contents
reference source is 
https://github.com/riscv-software-src/riscv-tests.git

This repository assumes that the riscv-gnu-toolchain package is installed, and the RISCV environment variable is set to the RISCV tools install path.

each test program should include risc_test.h header file, which defines the macro used by the TVM(Test Virtual Machines). 

##riscv-tests/isa/rv64ui/add.S
```
#include "riscv_test.h"
#include "test_macros.h"

RVTEST_RV64U
RVTEST_CODE_BEGIN

  #-------------------------------------------------------------
  # Arithmetic tests
  #-------------------------------------------------------------

  TEST_RR_OP( 2,  add, 0x00000000, 0x00000000, 0x00000000 );
  TEST_RR_OP( 3,  add, 0x00000002, 0x00000001, 0x00000001 );
  TEST_RR_OP( 4,  add, 0x0000000a, 0x00000003, 0x00000007 );
```

it has User-Level TVM ans Supervisor-Level TVMs. 
i will use user-level and rv32u*, rv64u* stands for user level test programs. 
rv32ui is my target ISA test program and it is same with rv64ui as assembly test program.

my idea is bring each instruction test .hex and use it
riscv-test calls gnu toolchain and it compile the test program and make .hex file
